      • getSQLData

        public com.github.yeetmanlord.zeta_core.sql.values.Row getSQLData()
        Gets the data of this GameEvent in a Row format.
        Returns:
        The data of this GameEvent
        See Also:
        Row
        Implementation Note:
        Extra data in a row is converted to a JSON string and stored in the EXTRA column, however once the data is loaded the data is "flattened" and put into the row. This is done to make it easier to read the data in a database. So, you store your data in key MY_DATA and on read you can just get the value of MY_DATA and not have to parse a JSON string.
